message.content: It is not possible to provide a definitive answer on what most women in Australia think of divorce, as opinions on this topic can vary greatly among individuals. However, it can be said that divorce is generally seen as a personal decision that women have the right to make if they are unhappy in their marriage. Many women in Australia believe that divorce can be a means to escape an unhealthy or abusive relationship and seek a better future for themselves and their children. Additionally, there is a growing acceptance of divorce as a normal part of life, and women are often encouraged to prioritize their own happiness and well-being. However, it is important to note that attitudes towards divorce can differ based on cultural, religious, and personal beliefs, and not all women may share the same perspective.
